ASK_USER=Ask the user directly in the chat. Use clear follow-up questions if needed.
SKILLS_DIR=~/.config/opencode/skills
RULES_SOURCE=`AGENTS.md` files in project (root + nested) and global `~/.config/opencode/AGENTS.md`. Also supports Claude Code compatibility via `CLAUDE.md` files.
DISPATCH_AGENT=Use the Skill tool to load and invoke specialized skills. Skills are defined as folders with SKILL.md in `.opencode/skills/` or global `~/.config/opencode/skills/`. Each skill has name and description visible in Skill tool.
PROGRESS_TOOL=Track progress via clear status messages in chat. No dedicated todo/checklist tool available - use explicit task completion announcements.
FILE_DISCOVERY=For file discovery, use Glob for patterns and Grep for content search. Do not fall back to shell commands unless no dedicated tool is available.
WEB_RESEARCH=Use WebSearch to find information and WebFetch to read specific URLs. Prefer official documentation over blog posts.
DISPATCH_RESEARCHER=Use Task tool with general subagent type to dispatch research tasks. Define research requirements in the prompt with specific deliverables.